Magal Soars Most in 3 Years in Tel Aviv on African Cup Contract

-- B y   S u s a n   L e r n e r
-- 
2011-05-31T15:43:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-31/magal-soars-most-in-3-years-in-tel-aviv-on-african-cup-contract.html
Magal Security Systems Ltd. (MAGS)  surged
the most in more than three years in  Tel Aviv  trading after the
computerized security systems maker won a $35.5 million order.  The shares advanced 17 percent, the most since January
2008, to 12.41 shekels at the 4:30 p.m. close in Tel Aviv. U.S.-
traded share jumped 8.4 percent to $3.34 at 11:32 a.m. in New
York.  Magal will supply a fully integrated security system
covering multiple sites for the African Cup of Nations Football
Championship in January 2012, the Yehud, Israel-based company
said.  Separately, Magal said its first-quarter loss narrowed to
$1.6 million from $2.4 million.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Susan Lerner in Jerusalem at 
